article.headline: Creighton 79, Indiana St. 61
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- P'Allen Stinnett scored 22 points and Booker Woodfox added 17 as Creighton held off Indiana State in a 79-61 victory Wednesday in the Missouri Valley Conference. Harry Marshall led Indiana State (3-10, 1-1 MVC) with 15 points while Rashad Reed had 11 points for the Sycamores. Creighton (12-2, 2-0) led throughout the first half, enjoying up to a 14-point edge before ending the half with a 40-29 advantage. The Sycamores outscored the Bluejays 13-6 in the first four minutes of the second half to come within four points, 46-42. But in the remaining nine minutes, Creighton outscored Indiana State 20-12 to seal the Bluejays' win. Creighton shot 48 percent from field-goal range for the game while the Sycamores managed just 32 percent. Creighton was also 9-for-9 from the free-throw line.
